### Indonesian Cone-Shaped Rice Dish

This particular article concerns itself with the [Indonesian](/Indonesian_cuisine) rice dish known as [Tumpeng](/Tumpeng). For the decidedly different Malaysian rice dish, which, frankly, bears only a superficial resemblance, one might consult [Nasi tumpang](/Nasi_tumpang).

***

**[Tumpeng](/Tumpeng)**
[Tumpeng](/Tumpeng): a monument of cone-shaped rice, grudgingly surrounded by an assortment of [Indonesian dishes](/List_of_Indonesian_dishes).
**Course** Main course
**Place of origin** [Indonesia](/Indonesia)
**Region or state** [Java](/Java), Nationwide
**Associated [cuisine](/List_of_cuisines)** [Indonesia](/Indonesian_cuisine)
**Serving temperature** Hot or room temperature
**Main ingredients** Cone-shaped rice (often [yellow rice](/Nasi_kuning) or [uduk rice](/Nasi_uduk)), [urab](/Urab) (vegetables in shredded coconut), [fried chicken](/Fried_chicken), fried tempeh, boiled marble egg, shredded omelette, salted [anchovy](/Anchovy), and peanuts
**Variations** Tumpeng robyong, tumpeng putih, tumpeng nasi uduk, tumpeng slametan (nasi kuning)

